speech.blockquote:
That, notwithstanding anything in the Standing Orders relative to Public Business: The Seanad on its rising on Thursday, 3rd December, 2020, shall adjourn until 10.30 a.m. on Tuesday, 8th December, 2020 and the following arrangements shall apply: (a) The Order of Business shall be proposed at 10.30 a.m. in the Dáil Chamber;
(b) Commencement matters shall be taken at 1.30 p.m. in the Seanad Chamber, and up to six matters may be selected by the Cathaoirleach for discussion;
(c) Business ordered to be taken subsequent to commencement matters, shall be taken in the Seanad Chamber.”
